input.prompt:
Generate 5 sample documents for the Civil Engineering domain to add to the samples/ directory. Each document should be 400-800 words and cover different civil engineering topics.

Create these files in samples/civil_engineering/:
1. structural_analysis_basics.txt - Load types, stress, strain, structural systems
2. foundation_engineering.txt - Soil mechanics, foundation types, bearing capacity
3. bridge_design_principles.txt - Bridge types, load distribution, materials
4. concrete_technology.txt - Mix design, curing, reinforcement, durability
5. highway_design.txt - Geometric design, pavement types, drainage

Each document should:
- Use domain-specific terminology naturally
- Include real engineering concepts and formulas where appropriate
- Be educational and substantive (not placeholder text)
- Follow this format: Title, Overview section, Key Principles section, Applications section

Create the directory if needed: mkdir -p samples/civil_engineering

Write authentic content - you have expertise in civil engineering. This is for training a specialized micro-model.
